15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 19 O.S. 2021, Section 510, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 510. A. Any person, otherwise qualified, who has been
19 a resident of the State of Oklahoma for two (2) years, has been a
20 registered voter of the party whose nomination he or she seeks, or a
21 registered Independent, within the county from which such person
22 seeks election for the six (6) months next preceding the first day
23 of the filing period, is at least twenty-five (25) years of age next
24 preceding the date of filing for office, possesses at least a high
