3 prior to the date of filing for the office of county sheriff, shall
4 be eligible to hold the office of county sheriff or to file
5 therefor. Within twelve (12) months of taking office, all newly
6 elected or appointed sheriffs shall complete a sheriff's
7 administrative school which has been developed by the Oklahoma
8 Sheriffs' Association and which has been approved by the Council on
9 Law Enforcement Education and Training (CLEET). Failure to complete
10 the sheriff's administrative school within the specified period
11 shall preclude the new sheriff from obtaining CLEET certification.
12 New sheriffs with prior CLEET certification, who fail to attend the
13 sheriff's administrative school, shall have their CLEET
14 certification revoked. Provided, however, the provisions of this
15 section relating to qualifications shall not apply to any person
16 serving as a county sheriff or to any person previously serving as
17 county sheriff prior to the adoption of this statute.
18 For purposes of this section, "peace officer" shall mean a full-
19 time duly appointed or elected officer who is paid for working more
20 than twenty-five (25) hours per week and whose duties are to
21 preserve the public peace, protect life and property, prevent crime,
22 serve warrants, and enforce state, federal or military laws and
23 local ordinances of this state or any political subdivision thereof.
